-- Japan PM says not targeting FX levels in intervention
-- 
-- Sun Feb 12, 2012 8:23pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/02/13/us-japan-economy-noda-idUSTRE81C03020120213

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Japanese Prime Minister Yoshihiko Noda said on Monday Tokyo does not have a specific currency level in mind when intervening in the currency market. 
 Any action in the currency market is aimed against disorderly and excessive market moves, Noda told parliament. (Reporting by  Leika Kihara ; Editing by  Michael Watson )